# Why Security Matters

Your app stores:

* Blood reports
* Personal information
* AI summaries
* Health history

Users should feel confident that only they can access their data.

---

# Security Flow

```text
User Opens App
        │
        ▼
Login
        │
        ▼
Authentication
        │
        ▼
Access Granted
        │
        ▼
View Reports
```

If authentication fails:

```text
Wrong Password

↓

Show Error

↓

Try Again
```

---

# User Authentication

For the MVP, support:

* Email + Password

In future versions, you can add:

* Google Sign-In
* Apple Sign-In
* Phone OTP

---

# Password Rules

Encourage strong passwords.

Example:

```text
Minimum 8 characters

At least:

✓ One uppercase letter

✓ One lowercase letter

✓ One number

✓ One special character
```

Example:

```text
Health@2026
```

---

# Password Storage

Never store passwords as plain text.

Bad:

```text
Password

Health123
```

Good:

```text
Encrypted Password Hash
```

Even if someone accessed the database, they shouldn't be able to read passwords.

---

# Report Storage

Every uploaded PDF should be stored securely.

```text
User

↓

Report

↓

Secure Cloud Storage
```

Users should never be able to access another user's reports.

---

# Access Control

Example:

```text
User A

↓

Can View

↓

User A Reports
```

But:

```text
User A

↓

Cannot View

↓

User B Reports
```

Every request should verify the logged-in user.

---

# Data Encryption

Sensitive information should be encrypted while stored.

Examples:

* Blood reports
* Personal details
* AI summaries

Encryption protects data even if storage is compromised.

---

# Secure Communication

All communication between:

* Mobile App
* Backend
* AI Service
* Cloud Storage

should use encrypted connections (HTTPS).

```text
App

⇄ HTTPS ⇄

Backend

⇄ HTTPS ⇄

Cloud
```

---

# Session Management

After login:

The app receives a secure session or access token.

```text
Login

↓

Access Token

↓

Open App
```

When the token expires:

```text
Ask user to log in again.
```

---

# Logout

When the user taps:

```text
Logout
```

The app should:

* Remove the session
* Return to the Login screen

Simple but important.

---

# If the Phone is Lost

A common question:

> "What happens if someone steals my phone?"

The answer:

Without the account password (or future biometric authentication), they shouldn't be able to access the user's reports.

---

# Delete Account

Users should always have the option to delete their account.

Example:

```text
Delete Account

Are you sure?

This will permanently delete:

• Reports

• AI Summaries

• Account Information

[Cancel]

[Delete]
```

---

# Privacy Policy

Your app should clearly explain:

* What data is collected
* Why it is collected
* How it is stored
* Whether it is shared
* How users can request deletion

Transparency builds trust.

---

# Backups

Imagine your server crashes.

Without backups:

Everything is lost.

With backups:

```text
Database

↓

Automatic Backup

↓

Restore
```

Even for an MVP, regular backups are essential.

---

# Audit Log (Future)

Keep a record of important actions.

Example:

```text
15 Jul 2026

Report Uploaded

------------------

15 Jul 2026

OCR Completed

------------------

15 Jul 2026

User Edited Hemoglobin

------------------

15 Jul 2026

AI Summary Generated
```

This is useful for debugging and improving the app.

---

